Merge pull request #10 from scorebuilders/2_scoreForm

Collects score data & posts to API, then bumps user to report page + lots of little things :)
now injecting WHATWG fetch polyfill whenever fetch identifier is seen via webpack
cosmetic tweak to scale default word
closes #2, added props for updating score payload + some "fetch"-ing code that pushes scores to the API; TODO - validation & prevent multiple submissions

Merge pull request #9 from scorebuilders/4_webpackdevserver

configured webpack dev server to support history API + routing to index.html

ok now it works for real. BONUS: react-router just fucking works; accomplished by adding "--history-api-fallback --output-public-path /" to our entry; maybe TODO - add those commands to webpack config
added flag to activate historyApiFallback which redirects all requests to /webpack-dev-server/ and uses index.html, which allows HMR for dev purposes
did some styling and what not
added boostrap + fonts + webpack tweaks for svg/font + new loaders
rough UI for scoring page w/some fun updating labels
